Boston Scientific to Acquire EndoChoice for $210 Million
Medical-device maker offering 90% premium for EndoChoice in deal that expands its endoscopy business

 






By

Joshua Jamerson


Joshua Jamerson
The Wall Street Journal
BiographyJoshua Jamerson
@joshjame
joshua.jamerson@wsj.com




  Sept. 27, 2016 7:31 a.m. ET





Medical-devices company Boston Scientific Corp. on Tuesday said it agreed to buy EndoChoice Holdings Inc. for roughly $210 million, expanding its endoscopy business as sales of some products have slowed. Boston Scientific said it would pay $8 a share in cash for EndoChoice, a 90% premium to its closing price of $4.22 a share on Monday.  Boston Scientific, based in Marlborough, Mass., has diversified its product offerings in...
  


